subSubSection.paragraph:
Color of holotype in preservative (
Fig. 3
): In ethanol, the dorsum is entirely dark brown; the lips, canthus rostralis, and the supratympanic fold are cream. The groin, posterior surfaces of the thighs, concealed surfaces of the shanks, and the dorsal surfaces of the feet are dark brown with irregular cream blotches. The throat, chest, belly, and, palmar and plantar surfaces are cream with scattered, irregular brown blotches on the belly.
